    "## Finding interesting mountains\n",
    "\n",
    "We can find relevant mountains with metadata and their geographical coordinates by looking at the various lists which [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Lists_of_mountains_of_Switzerland) provides."

   ],
   "source": [
    "df_mountains = pd.read_html(\n",
    "    \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prominent_mountains_of_Switzerland\"\n",
    ")[4]\n",
    "\n",
    "# it requires some extra engineering to get their latitude and longitude in a useable format\n",
    "def extract_coords(x):\n",
    "    lat_raw, lng_raw = x.split(\" \")\n",
    "    return float(lat_raw[1:-2]), float(\n",
    "        lng_raw[:-2]\n",
    "    )  # invisible character '\\ufeff' in front of lat\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df_mountains = df_mountains.assign(\n",
    "    coords=lambda x: x[\"Coordinates\"].str.split(\" / \").str[-1].apply(extract_coords)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_mountains.rename(\n",
    "    columns={\n",
    "        \"Mountain\": \"name\",\n",
    "        \"Height(m)[2]\": \"height_m\",\n",
    "        \"Prom.(m)[2]\": \"prominence_m\",\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    inplace=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_mountains = gpd.GeoDataFrame(\n",
    "    df_mountains,\n",
    "    geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(\n",
    "        df_mountains[\"coords\"].str[1], df_mountains[\"coords\"].str[0]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    ")\n",
    "df_mountains.set_crs(epsg=4326, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_mountains.head()"
   ]
  },

    "### Subset to interesting mountains\n",
    "\n",
    "To make the visualization feasible, we'll restrict ourselves to a subset of subjectively interesting mountains.\n",
    "We consider a mountain to be interesting if it is high, isolated and far away from the border (such that we can obtain the complete height profile of its surrounding region)."
   ]

   "source": [
    "tmp = df_switzerland.to_crs(epsg=3310).boundary\n",
    "df_mountains[\"distance_swiss_border\"] = df_mountains.to_crs(epsg=3310).geometry.apply(\n",
    "    lambda g: tmp.distance(g)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_mountains.sort_values(\"distance_swiss_border\").head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "exterior-deficit",

   "source": [
    "## Retrieve topological height profiles\n",
    "\n",
    "Once we have identified all mountains we are interested in, we can retrieve the height profiles of them and their surroundings from the [swissALTI3D](https://www.swisstopo.admin.ch/en/geodata/height/alti3d.html) data resource."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "major-excess",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Helper functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "virtual-heath",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def download_geotiff(x, y, dest_dir=Path(\"resources\"), year=2020):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Helper function to download a GeoTIFF at a given spatial index.\"\"\"\n",
    "    dest_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    fname = f\"swissalti3d_{year}_{x}-{y}_2_2056_5728.tif\"\n",
    "    target = dest_dir / fname\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not target.exists():\n",
    "        url = f\"https://data.geo.admin.ch/ch.swisstopo.swissalti3d/swissalti3d_{year}_{x}-{y}/{fname}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            sh.wget(\"-P\", str(dest_dir), url, _fg=True)\n",
    "        except sh.ErrorReturnCode_8:\n",
    "            if year == 2010:\n",
    "                print(f\"No topolgical data found for coordinates {x}, {y} ({url})\")\n",
    "                return None\n",
    "\n",
    "            next_year = year - 1\n",
    "            #             print(f\"Warning: {url} does not exist, trying again with previous year ({year} -> {next_year})\")\n",
    "            return download_geotiff(x, y, dest_dir=dest_dir, year=next_year)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return target\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_grid(latlong_coords, size=3):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Helper function of generate spatial index grid from latitude/longitude coordinates.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # infer the grid's spatial coordinates\n",
    "    dst_crs = rasterio.crs.CRS.from_epsg(2056)\n",
    "    transformer = Transformer.from_crs(\"epsg:4326\", dst_crs)\n",
    "\n",
    "    spatial_coords = transformer.transform(*latlong_coords)\n",
    "    swisstopo_coords = tuple(np.floor(sc / 1000).astype(int) for sc in spatial_coords)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # generate grid ranges\n",
    "    x_range = np.arange(swisstopo_coords[0] - size, swisstopo_coords[0] + size)\n",
    "    y_range = np.arange(swisstopo_coords[1] - size, swisstopo_coords[1] + size)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # return grid as list of tuples\n",
    "    grid = np.meshgrid(x_range, y_range)\n",
    "    return np.append(grid[0].reshape(-1, 1), grid[1].reshape(-1, 1), axis=1)"
   ]
  },

    "fname_dict = {}\n",
    "for row in tqdm(\n",
    "    df_mountains.itertuples(), total=df_mountains.shape[0], desc=\"Retrieve GeoTIFFs\"\n",
    "):\n",

    "    for x, y in tqdm(grid_coord_list, desc=f\"{row.name} {row.coords}\"):\n",
    "        fname = download_geotiff(x, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if fname is not None:\n",
    "            fname_dict[mnt].append(fname)"

    "def merge_geotiffs(fname_list):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Read multiple GeoTIFFs and merge them into single matrix.\"\"\"\n",
    "    dataset_list = [rasterio.open(fname) for fname in fname_list]\n",
    "    mosaic, out_trans = merge(dataset_list)\n",
    "    mosaic[mosaic == -9999] = np.nan  # clean broken values\n",
    "\n",
    "    crs_list = [dataset.crs for dataset in dataset_list]\n",
    "    assert len(set(crs_list)) == 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    return mosaic, out_trans, crs_list[0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "royal-blind",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "noticed-console",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Transform data\n",
    "\n",
    "We will now center each matrix on its point of highest elevation and make a circular cut out."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "fitting-shell",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_circle_indices(matrix, radius):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Get coordinates of all points falling outside of circle.\"\"\"\n",
    "    x0, y0 = np.unravel_index(matrix.argmax(), matrix.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "    xs, ys = np.meshgrid(np.arange(matrix.shape[0]), np.arange(matrix.shape[1]))\n",
    "    rs = np.sqrt((xs - x0) ** 2 + (ys - y0) ** 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return xs[rs > radius], ys[rs > radius]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def focus_matrix(matrix):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create circular cut out of given matrix.\"\"\"\n",
    "    matrix = matrix.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # set values outside circle to NaN\n",
    "    xs, ys = get_circle_indices(matrix, 800)\n",
    "    matrix[xs, ys] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "    # remove rows/columns which are all NaN now\n",
    "    matrix = matrix[:, ~np.isnan(matrix).all(axis=0)]\n",
    "    matrix = matrix[~np.isnan(matrix).all(axis=1), :]\n",
    "\n",
    "    return matrix"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tired-punishment",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### 3D view\n",
    "\n",
    "A more interactive and appealing visualization can be achieved by creating 3D meshes from the height data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "breathing-local",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Create vertex and face list"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "smoking-steering",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_mesh(matrix):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Generate vertex, face and color list for given value matrix.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # generate vertex list\n",
    "    vertex_list = []\n",
    "    for x, y in np.ndindex(matrix.shape):\n",
    "        if not np.isnan(matrix[x, y]):\n",
    "            vertex_list.append((x, y, matrix[x, y]))\n",
    "    vertex_list = np.asarray(vertex_list)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # generate color list\n",
    "    color_list = np.asarray(\n",
    "        [\n",
    "            matrix[x, y]\n",
    "            for x, y in np.ndindex(matrix.shape)\n",
    "            if not np.isnan(matrix[x, y])\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # generate face list\n",
    "    dela = Delaunay(vertex_list[:, :2])\n",
    "\n",
    "    face_list = []\n",
    "    for tri in dela.simplices:\n",
    "        face_list.append(tri)\n",
    "    face_list = np.asarray(face_list)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # finalize\n",
    "    return vertex_list, face_list, color_list"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "peripheral-burden",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "c6ebcf60e6f14f4dbdab336065592c61",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "Generate meshes:   0%|          | 0/11 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mesh_dict = {}\n",
    "for mnt, (matrix, _, _) in tqdm(profile_dict.items(), desc=\"Generate meshes\"):\n",
    "    mesh_dict[mnt] = create_mesh(matrix)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [

   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Simplify mesh\n",
    "\n",
    "To be able to render multiple meshes simultaneously in an efficient manner, we simplify their structure (i.e. remove vertices and faces while retaining approximate visual accuracy).\n",
    "\n",
    "We start by putting all (selected) mountains into a single coordinate system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "major-clarity",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mountain_selection = [\"Piz Kesch/Piz d'Es-Cha\", \"Tödi (Piz Russein)\", \"Finsteraarhorn\"]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "cognitive-timeline",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "0cb418e2cfad49678e92285fd8ef26f9",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/11 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "translation_matrix_dict = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "next_offset = 0\n",
    "for mnt, (matrix, _, _) in tqdm(profile_dict.items()):\n",
    "    if mnt not in mountain_selection:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "\n",
    "    cur_vertices = mesh_dict[mnt][0]\n",
    "    offset_mat = np.zeros_like(cur_vertices)\n",
    "\n",
    "    offset_mat[:, 0] = next_offset\n",
    "    next_offset += matrix.shape[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    translation_matrix_dict[mnt] = offset_mat"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "reliable-shanghai",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "eb4d3b0c956a4911ab0ec9d88ac52a72",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/11 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "all_vertices, all_faces, all_colors = [], [], []\n",
    "\n",
    "for mnt, (vertex_list, face_list, color_list) in tqdm(mesh_dict.items()):\n",
    "    if mnt not in mountain_selection:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "\n",
    "    translation_matrix = translation_matrix_dict[mnt]\n",
    "    translation_matrix[:, -1] = -vertex_list[\n",
    "        :, -1\n",
    "    ].min()  # make all mountains start at same height\n",
    "\n",
    "    all_faces.extend(face_list + len(all_vertices))\n",
    "    all_vertices.extend(vertex_list + translation_matrix)\n",
    "    all_colors.extend(color_list)\n",
    "\n",
    "all_vertices = np.asarray(all_vertices)\n",
    "all_faces = np.asarray(all_faces)\n",
    "all_colors = np.asarray(all_colors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "danish-manhattan",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Next, we use MeshLab to simplify our meshes. For use in other programs, we also save the (simplified) meshes to an OBJ file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "exclusive-hybrid",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "vertices/faces 6031719 12060852\n",
      "vertices/faces 604335 1206084\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "CPU times: user 5min 54s, sys: 23 s, total: 6min 17s\n",
      "Wall time: 6min 18s\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%%time\n",
    "ms = pymeshlab.MeshSet()\n",
    "\n",
    "mesh = pymeshlab.Mesh(all_vertices, all_faces)\n",
    "ms.add_mesh(mesh, \"surface\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\n",
    "    \"vertices/faces\", ms.current_mesh().vertex_number(), ms.current_mesh().face_number()\n",
    ")\n",
    "ms.apply_filter(\n",
    "    \"simplification_quadric_edge_collapse_decimation\",\n",
    "    targetperc=0.1,\n",
    "    preserveboundary=True,\n",
    "    preservenormal=True,\n",
    "    preservetopology=True,\n",
    "    planarquadric=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\n",
    "    \"vertices/faces\", ms.current_mesh().vertex_number(), ms.current_mesh().face_number()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ms.save_current_mesh(\"mountain_meshes.obj\")"
   ]
  },
